1
00:00:09,343 --> 00:00:10,427
(BELL RINGING)

2
00:00:10,511 --> 00:00:13,597
-Two minutes to curtain up, come on!
-MAN: Two minutes to curtain up.

3
00:00:13,680 --> 00:00:16,934
-Where's Tallulah?
-Where do you think?

4
00:00:17,434 --> 00:00:20,187
Hey, Tallulah, leave him alone!

5
00:00:26,944 --> 00:00:29,404
It's nearly show time, Laszlo,
I gotta go.

6
00:00:29,488 --> 00:00:31,198
Just promise me
you'll come on Sunday, okay?

7
00:00:31,281 --> 00:00:33,450
My mother will kill me
if she doesn't get to meet you.

8
00:00:33,575 --> 00:00:35,327
What if she doesn't like me?

9
00:00:35,452 --> 00:00:38,622
Tallulah, she'll love you
just as much as I do.

10
00:00:39,289 --> 00:00:42,459
Oh! You say the sweetest things.

11
00:00:42,543 --> 00:00:45,963
But it's true. Now promise me.
Sunday, you'll come?

12
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:49,591
I promise. Cross my heart.

13
00:00:51,009 --> 00:00:55,889
Oh, here take this, sweetheart.
Wear it on stage and think of me.

14
00:00:55,973 --> 00:00:57,057
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

15
00:00:57,140 --> 00:01:00,519
-Tallulah!
-I'm coming! Quit yelling!

16
00:01:02,521 --> 00:01:04,064
How do I look?

17
00:01:07,526 --> 00:01:09,027
Like an angel.

18
00:01:18,745 --> 00:01:20,872
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

19
00:01:20,998 --> 00:01:25,210
-TALLULAH: Wish me luck, Laszlo.
-Break a leg, sweetheart.

20
00:01:29,006 --> 00:01:30,382
(SNORTING)

21
00:01:32,050 --> 00:01:33,635
Tallulah?

22
00:01:42,436 --> 00:01:43,854
(SNORTING)

23
00:01:45,814 --> 00:01:47,357
Who's there?

24
00:01:53,363 --> 00:01:54,740
(SNORTING)

25
00:01:57,701 --> 00:01:58,952
Hello?

26
00:02:00,662 --> 00:02:02,039
Hello?

27
00:02:20,390 --> 00:02:22,351
(GRUNTING)

28
00:02:22,434 --> 00:02:25,854
Who's there? Who are you?

29
00:02:31,234 --> 00:02:32,527
(GASPING)

30
00:02:39,868 --> 00:02:42,663
(SQUEALING)

31
00:02:42,746 --> 00:02:45,707
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

32
00:03:22,119 --> 00:03:23,787
(WHOOSHING)

33
00:03:32,337 --> 00:03:36,049
-Where are we?
-Ah! Smell that Atlantic breeze.

34
00:03:36,133 --> 00:03:39,761
Nice and cold. Lovely!
Martha, have you met my friend?

35
00:03:40,762 --> 00:03:44,766
MARTHA: Is that... Oh, my God,
that's the Statue of Liberty!

36
00:03:44,850 --> 00:03:47,227
Gateway to the New World.

37
00:03:47,310 --> 00:03:49,271
"Give me your tired, your poor

38
00:03:49,354 --> 00:03:52,941
"Your huddled masses
yearning to breathe free."”

39
00:03:53,024 --> 00:03:56,361
That's so brilliant.
I've always wanted to go to New York.

40
00:03:56,445 --> 00:03:59,573
I mean, the real New York,
not the new, new, new one.

41
00:03:59,656 --> 00:04:02,325
Well, there's the genuine article.

42
00:04:02,868 --> 00:04:04,786
So good, they named it twice.

43
00:04:04,870 --> 00:04:07,289
Mind you,
it was New Amsterdam, originally.

44
00:04:07,372 --> 00:04:09,499
Harder to say twice,
no wonder it didn't catch on.

45
00:04:09,624 --> 00:04:13,044
-New Amsterdam, New Amsterdam.
-Wonder what year it is?

46
00:04:13,128 --> 00:04:15,547
'Cause look, the Empire State Building's
not even finished yet.

47
00:04:15,630 --> 00:04:18,717
Work in progress. They've still got
a couple of floors to go,

48
00:04:18,842 --> 00:04:22,095
and if I know my history,
that makes the date somewhere around...

49
00:04:22,179 --> 00:04:24,139
November 1st, 1930.

50
00:04:24,639 --> 00:04:26,475
You're getting good at this.

51
00:04:26,558 --> 00:04:28,769
That's nearly 80 years ago.

52
00:04:28,852 --> 00:04:32,105
It's funny, 'cause you see those old
newsreels, all in black and white,

53
00:04:32,189 --> 00:04:35,233
like it's so far away, but here we are.

54
00:04:35,901 --> 00:04:37,819
It's real. It's now.

55
00:04:39,488 --> 00:04:41,823
Come on, you.
Where do you want go first?

56
00:04:41,907 --> 00:04:44,451
I think our detour just got longer.

57
00:04:44,534 --> 00:04:48,038
"Hooverville Mystery Deepens."”
What's Hooverville?

58
00:04:51,374 --> 00:04:55,212
Herbert Hoover, 31st President
of the USA, came to power a year ago.

59
00:04:55,337 --> 00:04:58,548
Up till then, New York was a boom town,
the Roaring Twenties. And then...

60
00:04:58,632 --> 00:05:01,092
The Wall Street Crash, yeah.
When was that, 19297

61
00:05:01,218 --> 00:05:03,261
Yeah. The whole economy
wiped out overnight.

62
00:05:03,345 --> 00:05:05,138
Thousands of people unemployed.

63
00:05:05,222 --> 00:05:08,517
All of a sudden, the huddled masses
doubled in number with nowhere to go.

64
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:10,977
So they ended up here in Central Park.

65
00:05:11,061 --> 00:05:15,774
What, they actually live in the park?
In the middle of the city?

66
00:05:24,533 --> 00:05:28,578
Ordinary people lost their jobs,

67
00:05:29,663 --> 00:05:32,666
couldn't pay the rent,
they lost everything.

68
00:05:34,501 --> 00:05:39,256
There are places like this all over
America. No one's helping them.

69
00:05:41,007 --> 00:05:43,552
You only come to Hooverville
when there's nowhere else to go.

70
00:05:43,635 --> 00:05:45,804
MAN: You thieving low life!

71
00:05:46,596 --> 00:05:49,891
All morning I wait in the bread line
for a single loaf...

72
00:05:49,975 --> 00:05:51,768
I didn't touch it.

73
00:05:52,060 --> 00:05:55,105
-Somebody stole it from me...
-Cut that out!

74
00:05:56,106 --> 00:05:58,859
Cut it out, right now.

75
00:05:58,942 --> 00:06:01,653
-He stole my bread!
-That's enough!

76
00:06:02,112 --> 00:06:03,822
Did you take it?

77
00:06:03,947 --> 00:06:07,075
I don't know what happened,
he just went crazy.

78
00:06:07,576 --> 00:06:09,286
That's enough!

79
00:06:11,663 --> 00:06:14,749
Now, think real careful
before you lie to me.

80
00:06:16,418 --> 00:06:18,420
I'm starving, Solomon.

81
00:06:24,718 --> 00:06:26,261
(PEOPLE EXCLAIMING)

82
00:06:26,344 --> 00:06:30,849
We all starving.
We all got family somewhere.

83
00:06:33,768 --> 00:06:37,355
No stealing and no fighting.
You know the rules.

84
00:06:38,148 --> 00:06:43,236
Thirteen years ago, I fought
in the Great War. A lot of us did.

85
00:06:43,445 --> 00:06:48,116
And the only reason we got through
because we stuck together.

86
00:06:49,576 --> 00:06:54,539
No matter how bad things get,
we still act like human beings.

87
00:06:54,998 --> 00:06:56,666
It's all we got.

88
00:07:01,004 --> 00:07:02,213
Come on.

89
00:07:03,381 --> 00:07:06,509
I suppose that makes
you the boss around here.

90
00:07:07,636 --> 00:07:10,889
And who might you be?

91
00:07:10,972 --> 00:07:14,184
-He's the Doctor, I'm Martha.
-A doctor?

92
00:07:14,726 --> 00:07:20,482
Well, we got stockbrokers,
we've got a lawyer,

93
00:07:21,191 --> 00:07:23,109
but you're the first doctor.

94
00:07:23,193 --> 00:07:26,279
The neighbourhood gets classier
by the day.

95
00:07:26,363 --> 00:07:28,156
How many people live here?

96
00:07:28,239 --> 00:07:32,994
Any one time, hundreds.
No place else to go.

97
00:07:33,078 --> 00:07:36,539
But I will say this about Hooverville,
we a truly equal society.

98
00:07:36,665 --> 00:07:40,502
Black, white,
all the same, all starving.

99
00:07:41,044 --> 00:07:44,214
So you're welcome, both of you.

100
00:07:45,548 --> 00:07:48,635
But tell me, Doctor,
you're a man of learning, right??

101
00:07:48,718 --> 00:07:51,012
Explain this to me.

102
00:07:53,098 --> 00:07:57,477
That there is going to be
the tallest building in the world.

103
00:07:57,560 --> 00:07:59,813
How come they can do that

104
00:07:59,896 --> 00:08:03,400
and we got people starving
in the heart of Manhattan?

105
00:08:11,741 --> 00:08:14,494
Right, a little more.

106
00:08:14,577 --> 00:08:16,496
Hoist!

107
00:08:17,330 --> 00:08:20,083
MAN: I'm telling you
the men won't stand for it.

108
00:08:20,208 --> 00:08:22,585
I mean, are you out of your mind?

109
00:08:22,669 --> 00:08:25,672
I got five hundred men
working seven days a week.

110
00:08:25,755 --> 00:08:28,842
They're flat out,
and you want us to go faster?

111
00:08:28,925 --> 00:08:31,011
The new masters demand it.

112
00:08:31,136 --> 00:08:33,596
But we're on schedule.
What's the problem?

113
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:35,807
Another month and we'll be done.

114
00:08:35,932 --> 00:08:40,437
The mast on this building
needs extra work completed by tonight.

115
00:08:40,562 --> 00:08:43,273
Tonight? No way. It's impossible.

116
00:08:43,398 --> 00:08:45,567
-That's an order.
-Yeah?

117
00:08:45,650 --> 00:08:50,030
Well, one word from me,
and every man on this site stops work.

118
00:08:50,113 --> 00:08:52,615
So go on, tell your masters that.

119
00:08:53,783 --> 00:08:57,370
If that's your attitude,
I think you should tell them yourself.

120
00:08:57,454 --> 00:09:01,583
Yeah? Well, I ain't afraid
of no man in a suit.

121
00:09:01,791 --> 00:09:05,045
These new bosses, what's their names?

122
00:09:05,128 --> 00:09:07,881
I think you could say
they're from out of town.

123
00:09:07,964 --> 00:09:10,842
-Italians?
-Bit further than that.

124
00:09:11,801 --> 00:09:15,221
-How much further?
-Beyond your imagination.

125
00:09:15,305 --> 00:09:18,308
Oh, what's that supposed to mean?
Who are they?

126
00:09:18,391 --> 00:09:21,478
Mr Diagoras, who are we working for?

127
00:09:26,816 --> 00:09:28,693
Behold your masters.

128
00:09:30,028 --> 00:09:31,988
(BELL DINGING)

129
00:09:44,084 --> 00:09:45,335
What the hell...

130
00:09:45,418 --> 00:09:49,255
I have been summoned. Explain.

131
00:09:49,380 --> 00:09:51,174
Explain!

132
00:09:51,257 --> 00:09:54,594
It can talk. How does it talk?

133
00:09:55,762 --> 00:09:58,515
And what the hell are they?
You gotta be kidding me?

134
00:09:58,598 --> 00:10:00,016
I'm sorry, my lord,

135
00:10:00,100 --> 00:10:03,728
but this man is refusing
to complete the work.

136
00:10:03,853 --> 00:10:05,939
Then we must replace him.

137
00:10:06,022 --> 00:10:08,441
Is anybody gonna tell me
what the hell is happening here?

138
00:10:08,525 --> 00:10:12,987
Use him.
Take him for the final experiment.

139
00:10:13,113 --> 00:10:16,241
What's going on? Let go. Let go of me.

140
00:10:16,324 --> 00:10:19,327
Let go of me. Get off of me, you freaks!

141
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:23,206
Mr Diagoras, will you tell them!
Mr Diagoras...

142
00:10:23,289 --> 00:10:28,378
The Empire State Building
must be completed in time.

143
00:10:29,379 --> 00:10:31,798
It will be, trust me.

144
00:10:31,881 --> 00:10:34,425
Labour is cheap
and that man can be replaced.

145
00:10:34,509 --> 00:10:36,344
The plan must not fail.

146
00:10:36,427 --> 00:10:40,306
We calculate the Gamma strike
has accelerated.

147
00:10:40,390 --> 00:10:44,853
-We need more bodies immediately!
-Yes, master.

148
00:10:51,651 --> 00:10:55,947
So, men going missing. Is this true?

149
00:10:58,408 --> 00:11:00,410
It's true all right.

150
00:11:03,788 --> 00:11:05,206
But what does missing mean?

151
00:11:05,290 --> 00:11:07,083
I mean, people must come and go here
all the time.

152
00:11:07,208 --> 00:11:09,085
It's not like anyone's keeping
a register.

153
00:11:09,210 --> 00:11:10,837
Come on in.

154
00:11:13,006 --> 00:11:15,884
-This is different.
-In what way?

155
00:11:17,594 --> 00:11:20,930
Someone takes them, at night.

156
00:11:21,014 --> 00:11:23,433
We hear something,
someone calls out for help.

157
00:11:23,558 --> 00:11:27,770
By the time we get there, they're gone.
Like they vanish into thin air.

158
00:11:27,854 --> 00:11:30,481
And you're sure someone's taking them?

159
00:11:30,565 --> 00:11:34,694
Doctor, when you've got next to nothing,
you hold on to the little you got.

160
00:11:34,777 --> 00:11:36,988
Knife, blanket, you take it with you.

161
00:11:37,071 --> 00:11:40,700
You don't leave bread uneaten,
a fire still burning.

162
00:11:40,783 --> 00:11:42,327
Have you been to the police?

163
00:11:42,452 --> 00:11:46,456
Yeah, we tried that.
Another deadbeat goes missing, big deal.

164
00:11:47,790 --> 00:11:50,919
So the question is
who's taking them and what for?

165
00:11:51,002 --> 00:11:54,464
Solomon! Solomon, Mr Diagoras is here.

166
00:11:56,966 --> 00:12:01,679
I need men, volunteers.
I've got a little work for you.

167
00:12:01,763 --> 00:12:04,599
And you sure look like
you could use the money.

168
00:12:04,682 --> 00:12:06,851
-Yeah, what is the money?
-A dollar a day.

169
00:12:06,976 --> 00:12:08,102
(MEN LAUGHING)

170
00:12:08,186 --> 00:12:11,564
-What's the work?
-A little trip down the sewers.

171
00:12:11,648 --> 00:12:15,818
Got a tunnel collapsed,
needs clearing and fixing. Any takers?

172
00:12:15,944 --> 00:12:19,280
-Uh-uh.
-A dollar a day is a slave wage.

173
00:12:19,364 --> 00:12:20,490
MEN: Yeah, yeah!

174
00:12:20,573 --> 00:12:23,117
And men don't always come back up,
do they?

175
00:12:23,201 --> 00:12:25,078
Accidents happen.

176
00:12:25,161 --> 00:12:26,663
What do you mean,
what sort of accidents?

177
00:12:26,746 --> 00:12:28,831
You don't need the work, that's fine.

178
00:12:28,957 --> 00:12:32,585
Anybody else? Enough with the questions.

179
00:12:32,669 --> 00:12:36,005
Oh, no, no, no.
I'm volunteering. I'll go.

180
00:12:36,589 --> 00:12:37,757
I'll kill you for this.

181
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:38,925
(CHUCKLES)

182
00:12:39,008 --> 00:12:41,010
DIAGORAS: Anybody else?

183
00:12:45,181 --> 00:12:49,978
Turn left, go about half a mile,
follow tunnel 273,

184
00:12:50,061 --> 00:12:51,980
the fall's right ahead of you.
You can't miss it.

185
00:12:52,063 --> 00:12:54,274
And when do we get our dollar?

186
00:12:54,857 --> 00:12:58,027
-When you come back up.
-And if we don't come back up?

187
00:12:58,111 --> 00:13:00,196
Then I got no one to pay.

188
00:13:00,280 --> 00:13:03,700
-Don't worry, we'll be back.
-Let's hope so.

189
00:13:07,161 --> 00:13:08,746
FRANK: We gotta stick together.

190
00:13:08,871 --> 00:13:12,917
It's easy to get lost.
It's like a huge rabbit warren.

191
00:13:13,918 --> 00:13:16,421
You could hide an army down here.

192
00:13:19,382 --> 00:13:20,717
MARTHA: So, what about you, Frank?

193
00:13:20,842 --> 00:13:22,844
You're not from around these parts,
are you?

194
00:13:22,927 --> 00:13:25,013
(LAUGHING) Oh, you can talk.

195
00:13:25,096 --> 00:13:29,225
-No, I'm Tennessee, born and bred.
-So how come you're here?

196
00:13:29,350 --> 00:13:34,439
Oh, my Daddy died,
Momma couldn't afford to feed us all,

197
00:13:34,522 --> 00:13:37,066
so, I'm the oldest,
up to me to feed myself.

198
00:13:37,150 --> 00:13:40,111
So I put on my coat,
hitched up here on the railroads.

199
00:13:40,194 --> 00:13:43,781
There's a whole lot of runaways
in the camp, younger than me

200
00:13:43,906 --> 00:13:47,368
from all over,
Missouri, Oklahoma, Texas.

201
00:13:47,452 --> 00:13:50,413
Solomon keeps a look out for us.

202
00:13:51,706 --> 00:13:55,626
So, what about you?
You're a long way from home.

203
00:13:55,918 --> 00:14:00,840
-Yeah, I'm just a hitcher, too.
-You stick with me, you'll be all right.

204
00:14:00,923 --> 00:14:04,260
So this Diagoras bloke, who is he, then?

205
00:14:04,385 --> 00:14:07,555
Couple of months ago,
he was just another foreman.

206
00:14:07,638 --> 00:14:11,142
Now seems like
he's running most of Manhattan.

207
00:14:11,225 --> 00:14:15,897
-How'd he manage that, then?
-These are strange times.

208
00:14:15,980 --> 00:14:18,483
A man can go from being
the king of the hill

209
00:14:18,566 --> 00:14:21,527
to the lowest of the low overnight.

210
00:14:21,611 --> 00:14:23,529
Guess for some folks,
it works the other way around.

211
00:14:23,613 --> 00:14:25,281
Whoa!

212
00:14:28,034 --> 00:14:30,453
Is it radioactive, or something?

213
00:14:32,455 --> 00:14:34,457
(GAGGING)

214
00:14:34,540 --> 00:14:37,168
It's gone off, whatever it is.

215
00:14:39,921 --> 00:14:42,298
And you've got to pick it up.

216
00:14:44,300 --> 00:14:46,469
Shine your torch through it.

217
00:14:48,638 --> 00:14:53,643
Composite organic matter.
Martha, medical opinion?

218
00:14:54,185 --> 00:14:59,482
-It's not human, I know that.
-No. It's not.

219
00:15:00,817 --> 00:15:03,152
And I'll tell you something else.

220
00:15:03,236 --> 00:15:04,529
We must be at least half a mile in,

221
00:15:04,654 --> 00:15:07,573
I don't see any signs of a collapse,
do you?

222
00:15:07,657 --> 00:15:10,618
So why did Mr Diagoras
send us down here?

223
00:15:10,701 --> 00:15:12,954
Where are we now? What's up above?

224
00:15:13,037 --> 00:15:16,499
Well, we're right underneath Manhattan.

225
00:15:23,506 --> 00:15:28,010
DIAGORAS: And here, the crowning glory
of the Empire State Building,

226
00:15:28,094 --> 00:15:30,263
the mast itself.

227
00:15:30,346 --> 00:15:34,058
1,472 feet above New York.

228
00:15:34,142 --> 00:15:35,935
It's a beautiful thing, sir.

229
00:15:36,018 --> 00:15:38,604
And every single one of us
is proud of it.

230
00:15:38,688 --> 00:15:42,942
My wife says it's like a,
like a spire reaching into heaven.

231
00:15:43,025 --> 00:15:46,487
Except the gates of heaven
need a little decoration.

232
00:15:48,698 --> 00:15:54,537
These plates have gotta be fixed
to the mast, right to the base itself.

233
00:15:55,371 --> 00:15:58,666
That's okay. That's not too bad.
Shouldn't take too long.

234
00:15:58,749 --> 00:16:01,294
But the work has
gotta be finished tonight.

235
00:16:01,377 --> 00:16:03,045
-What, are you trying to kill us?
-It's not safe!

236
00:16:03,171 --> 00:16:04,547
We're flat out up there. Come on.

237
00:16:04,672 --> 00:16:06,632
Don't argue with me!

238
00:16:06,716 --> 00:16:08,718
But, sir, the men
can't work up there at night.

239
00:16:08,801 --> 00:16:12,638
It's freezing. Your hands go numb,
you lose your grip, you fall.

240
00:16:12,722 --> 00:16:14,474
You don't get it.

241
00:16:18,311 --> 00:16:22,732
If you won't work,
I can replace you like that.

242
00:16:28,237 --> 00:16:32,408
Now take those panels and get going.

243
00:16:41,375 --> 00:16:45,671
-What sort of metal is this, anyway?
-Don't ask questions. Just go.

244
00:16:57,433 --> 00:17:01,521
I don't care how cold it is,
how tired you are,

245
00:17:01,604 --> 00:17:04,273
just get out there and finish the job!

246
00:17:10,321 --> 00:17:15,201
The conductor must be complete
for our plan to succeed.

247
00:17:17,078 --> 00:17:19,539
Unemployment is such an incentive.

248
00:17:19,622 --> 00:17:21,707
It'll get done, don't worry.

249
00:17:21,791 --> 00:17:25,586
Daleks have no concept of worry.

250
00:17:25,670 --> 00:17:29,674
Yeah? Well, lucky you.

251
00:17:29,757 --> 00:17:32,593
This day is ending.

252
00:17:32,677 --> 00:17:37,598
Humankind is weak,
you shelter from the dark.

253
00:17:38,849 --> 00:17:43,187
And yet, you have built all this.

254
00:17:44,605 --> 00:17:46,315
That's progress.

255
00:17:46,941 --> 00:17:50,236
You gotta move with the times
or you get left behind.

256
00:17:50,319 --> 00:17:53,030
My planet is gone.

257
00:17:53,155 --> 00:17:55,992
Destroyed in a great war.

258
00:17:56,909 --> 00:18:01,455
Yet, versions of this city
stand throughout history.

259
00:18:01,539 --> 00:18:05,793
The human race always continues.

260
00:18:06,794 --> 00:18:10,881
We've had wars.
I've been a soldier myself.

261
00:18:12,133 --> 00:18:16,429
And I swore then I'd survive,
no matter what.

262
00:18:16,512 --> 00:18:19,640
You have rare ambition.

263
00:18:22,435 --> 00:18:28,024
I want to run this city, whatever
it takes. By any means necessary.

264
00:18:28,524 --> 00:18:32,236
You think like a Dalek.

265
00:18:32,361 --> 00:18:34,447
I'll take that as a compliment.

266
00:18:40,202 --> 00:18:45,166
This human is our best option.
Bring him to me.

267
00:18:45,249 --> 00:18:50,296
Your loyalty will be rewarded.
Come with me.

268
00:18:55,718 --> 00:19:01,015
Prepare the laboratory.
The final experiment will begin!

269
00:19:01,223 --> 00:19:02,808
We obey.

270
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:22,161
-Where are we going?
-You have been summoned by our leader.

271
00:19:22,244 --> 00:19:25,164
Oh, and about time, too.

272
00:19:51,399 --> 00:19:53,818
(SNORTING)

273
00:20:10,793 --> 00:20:14,255
I bring you the human.

274
00:20:15,131 --> 00:20:18,759
-I take it you're in charge?
-Correct.

275
00:20:18,843 --> 00:20:24,473
I am Dalek Sec.
Leader of the Cult of Skaro.

276
00:20:26,142 --> 00:20:30,354
Then, my Lord Sec,
I am honoured to meet you.

277
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:34,150
Ever since you first made
contact with me,

278
00:20:34,233 --> 00:20:37,319
transmitting your thoughts
into the corners of my mind,

279
00:20:37,403 --> 00:20:41,407
tempting me with such images,
such ideas,

280
00:20:41,490 --> 00:20:43,743
oh, sir, I'd always dreamt
that together...

281
00:20:43,826 --> 00:20:45,828
Cease talking.

282
00:20:45,953 --> 00:20:47,913
I just wanna let you know
how grateful I am...

283
00:20:47,997 --> 00:20:49,832
I said cease!

284
00:20:50,416 --> 00:20:53,669
Slaves! Secure the human.

285
00:20:53,753 --> 00:20:56,839
But you don't need to do that,
I'm on your side.

286
00:20:56,922 --> 00:21:00,676
I'm working with you.
I'm your partner! I'm your friend!

287
00:21:03,220 --> 00:21:06,974
We're way beyond half a mile.
There's no collapse, nothing.

288
00:21:07,057 --> 00:21:10,227
-That Diagoras bloke, was he lying?
-Looks like it.

289
00:21:10,352 --> 00:21:12,354
So why'd he want people
to come down here?

290
00:21:12,438 --> 00:21:14,732
Solomon, I think it's time
you took these two back.

291
00:21:14,815 --> 00:21:16,525
I'll be much quicker on my own.

292
00:21:16,650 --> 00:21:18,235
(SQUEALING)

293
00:21:18,360 --> 00:21:21,155
-What the hell was that?
-Hello?

294
00:21:21,238 --> 00:21:22,323
-Shh!
-SOLOMON: Frank!

295
00:21:22,406 --> 00:21:24,617
What if it's one
of the folk gone missing?

296
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:26,786
You'd be scared, half mad
down here on your own.

297
00:21:26,869 --> 00:21:28,412
You think they're still alive?

298
00:21:28,496 --> 00:21:32,082
Heck, we ain't seen no bodies down here.
Maybe they just got lost.

299
00:21:32,208 --> 00:21:34,251
(SQUEALING)

300
00:21:34,919 --> 00:21:36,754
I never heard nobody
make a sound like that.

301
00:21:36,837 --> 00:21:38,798
Where's it coming from?

302
00:21:42,718 --> 00:21:44,220
FRANK: Sounds like
there's more than one of them.

303
00:21:44,345 --> 00:21:47,723
-This way?
-No, that way.

304
00:21:51,227 --> 00:21:52,561
Doctor.

305
00:21:59,485 --> 00:22:01,111
Who are you?

306
00:22:02,696 --> 00:22:04,573
FRANK: Are you lost?

307
00:22:06,617 --> 00:22:08,536
Can you understand me?

308
00:22:10,037 --> 00:22:12,456
I've been thinking about
folk lost down here.

309
00:22:12,540 --> 00:22:16,961
It's all right, Frank, just stay back.
Let me have a look.

310
00:22:19,046 --> 00:22:21,924
He's got a point, though, my mate Frank.

311
00:22:22,383 --> 00:22:25,261
I'd hate to be stuck down here
on my own.

312
00:22:26,637 --> 00:22:32,810
We know the way out. Daylight.
If you come with us.

313
00:22:36,856 --> 00:22:39,900
Oh, but what are you?

314
00:22:39,984 --> 00:22:43,612
Is that some kind of carnival mask?

315
00:22:43,737 --> 00:22:45,364
No, it's real.

316
00:22:48,617 --> 00:22:50,035
I'm sorry.

317
00:22:51,996 --> 00:22:56,292
But listen to me. I promise I can help.

318
00:22:57,626 --> 00:22:59,128
Who did this to you?

319
00:22:59,211 --> 00:23:02,673
Doctor,
I think you'd better get back here.

320
00:23:04,550 --> 00:23:08,304
-Doctor!
-Actually, good point.

321
00:23:09,805 --> 00:23:13,392
-They're following you.
-Yeah, I noticed that, thanks.

322
00:23:15,019 --> 00:23:18,022
Right, then, Martha, Frank, Solomon.

323
00:23:18,606 --> 00:23:22,985
-MARTHA: What?
-I think, um, basically,

324
00:23:23,485 --> 00:23:25,362
run!

325
00:23:35,122 --> 00:23:37,708
-Where are we going?
-This way!

326
00:23:47,051 --> 00:23:49,595
There's a ladder. Come on!

327
00:23:59,104 --> 00:24:00,481
Frank!

328
00:24:12,117 --> 00:24:14,244
-Come on, Frank.
-Come on.

329
00:24:15,663 --> 00:24:17,164
SOLOMON: I got you.

330
00:24:17,247 --> 00:24:20,209
Come on! Come on!

331
00:24:20,292 --> 00:24:23,212
-Come on!
-Frank!

332
00:24:23,337 --> 00:24:25,881
-Frank!
-No!

333
00:24:28,801 --> 00:24:30,719
-We can't go after him.
-I've got to go back down!

334
00:24:30,803 --> 00:24:34,682
-We can't just leave him.
-No, I'm not losing anybody else!

335
00:24:34,765 --> 00:24:36,809
Those creatures were from hell!
From hell itself!

336
00:24:36,892 --> 00:24:41,313
If we go after him, they'll take us all!
There's nothing we can do.

337
00:24:42,481 --> 00:24:43,941
I'm sorry.

338
00:24:44,566 --> 00:24:47,194
All right then, put 'em up!

339
00:24:48,737 --> 00:24:51,865
Hands in the air and no funny business.

340
00:24:52,616 --> 00:24:55,494
Now, tell me, you shmucks,

341
00:24:55,744 --> 00:24:58,080
what have you done with Laszlo?

342
00:24:59,289 --> 00:25:02,292
-Who's Laszlo?
-Laszlo's my boyfriend.

343
00:25:03,460 --> 00:25:06,255
Was my boyfriend
until he disappeared two weeks ago.

344
00:25:06,338 --> 00:25:08,882
No letter, no goodbye, no nothing.

345
00:25:09,299 --> 00:25:13,887
And I'm not stupid. I know some guys
are just pigs, but not my Laszlo.

346
00:25:13,971 --> 00:25:16,890
I mean, what kind of guy asks you
to meet his mom before he vamooses?

347
00:25:16,974 --> 00:25:19,935
(STAMMERING) Might...might just help
if you put that down.

348
00:25:20,019 --> 00:25:21,520
Huh?

349
00:25:22,271 --> 00:25:23,355
Oh, sure.

350
00:25:23,439 --> 00:25:24,565
(EXCLAIMS)

351
00:25:24,648 --> 00:25:27,568
Oh, come on, it's not real.
It's just a prop.

352
00:25:27,651 --> 00:25:31,530
-It was either that or a spear.
-What do you think happened to Laszlo?

353
00:25:31,613 --> 00:25:36,410
I wish I knew. One minute he's there,
the next, zip, vanished.

354
00:25:36,493 --> 00:25:38,996
-Listen, what was your name?
-Tallulah.

355
00:25:39,121 --> 00:25:41,165
-Tallulah.
-Three "L's" and an "H".

356
00:25:41,248 --> 00:25:44,835
Right. We can try and find Laszlo,
but he's not the only one.

357
00:25:44,960 --> 00:25:46,837
There are people disappearing
every night.

358
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:51,091
And there are creatures.
Such creatures...

359
00:25:52,134 --> 00:25:55,429
-What do you mean, creatures?
-Look, listen, just trust me.

360
00:25:55,512 --> 00:25:59,892
Everyone is in danger.
I need to find out exactly what this is.

361
00:26:00,726 --> 00:26:03,812
Because then I'll know exactly
what we're fighting.

362
00:26:03,896 --> 00:26:05,355
Yeuch!

363
00:26:13,697 --> 00:26:18,452
-How about this? I found it backstage.
-Perfect.

364
00:26:18,827 --> 00:26:20,662
It's the capacitors I need.

365
00:26:20,788 --> 00:26:24,249
I'm just rigging up a crude, little
DNA scan for this beastie.

366
00:26:24,333 --> 00:26:27,086
If I can get a chromosomal reading,
I can find out where it's from.

367
00:26:27,169 --> 00:26:30,255
How about you, Doctor?
Where are you from?

368
00:26:30,339 --> 00:26:34,426
I been all over, I never heard
anybody talk like you.

369
00:26:34,510 --> 00:26:36,470
Just exactly who are you?

370
00:26:36,553 --> 00:26:40,808
-Oh, I'm just sort of passing by.
-I'm not a fool, Doctor.

371
00:26:42,726 --> 00:26:45,145
No. Sorry.

372
00:26:54,238 --> 00:26:56,156
I was scared, Doctor.

373
00:26:57,699 --> 00:27:02,371
I let 'em take Frank
"cause I was just so scared.

374
00:27:06,500 --> 00:27:08,293
I got to get back to Hooverville.

375
00:27:08,377 --> 00:27:10,963
With these creatures on the loose,
we gotta protect ourselves.

376
00:27:11,046 --> 00:27:13,757
-And no one else gonna help us.
-Good luck.

377
00:27:15,384 --> 00:27:19,263
I hope you find what you're looking for,
for all our sakes.

378
00:27:23,725 --> 00:27:27,646
Laszlo, he'd wait for me after the show.

379
00:27:27,729 --> 00:27:30,732
Walk me home, like I was a lady.

380
00:27:30,858 --> 00:27:32,985
He'd leave a flower for me
on my dressing table.

381
00:27:33,068 --> 00:27:35,320
Every day, just a single rosebud.

382
00:27:35,404 --> 00:27:37,865
Haven't you reported him missing?

383
00:27:37,948 --> 00:27:41,743
Sure, but he's just a stagehand,
who cares?

384
00:27:41,827 --> 00:27:45,372
-The management certainly don't.
-Can't you kick up a fuss or something?

385
00:27:45,455 --> 00:27:47,124
Okay, so then they fire me.

386
00:27:47,207 --> 00:27:50,752
But they'd listen to you,
you're one of the stars.

387
00:27:50,878 --> 00:27:54,464
Oh, honey, I got one song
in a back-street revue,

388
00:27:54,548 --> 00:27:56,550
and that's only
'cause Heidi Chicane broke her ankle,

389
00:27:56,633 --> 00:27:59,428
which had nothing to do with me
whatever anybody says.

390
00:27:59,511 --> 00:28:01,847
I can't afford to make a fuss.

391
00:28:02,681 --> 00:28:03,849
If I don't make this month's rent,

392
00:28:03,932 --> 00:28:05,976
then before you know it,
I'm in Hooverville.

393
00:28:06,059 --> 00:28:08,187
Okay, I get it.

394
00:28:08,312 --> 00:28:10,355
It's the Depression, sweetie.

395
00:28:10,439 --> 00:28:12,691
Your heart might break,
but the show goes on,

396
00:28:12,774 --> 00:28:15,277
'cause if it stops, you starve.

397
00:28:15,944 --> 00:28:18,322
Every night I have to go out there,

398
00:28:18,405 --> 00:28:23,285
sing, dance, keep going,
hoping he's gonna come back.

399
00:28:25,579 --> 00:28:26,955
I'm sorry.

400
00:28:29,333 --> 00:28:33,629
Hey, you're lucky, though.
You got yourself a forward-thinking guy

401
00:28:33,712 --> 00:28:39,009
-with that hot potato in the sharp suit.
-Oh, he's not... We're not together.

402
00:28:39,134 --> 00:28:43,555
Oh, sure you are. I've seen the way
you look at him. It's obvious.

403
00:28:43,639 --> 00:28:45,182
Not to him.

404
00:28:46,141 --> 00:28:51,521
Oh, I should have realised.
He's into musical theatre, huh?

405
00:28:51,605 --> 00:28:55,734
What a waste.
Still, you gotta live in hope.

406
00:28:55,817 --> 00:29:00,322
It's the only thing that's kept me
going, 'cause, well, look.

407
00:29:01,281 --> 00:29:03,992
On my dressing table every day still.

408
00:29:04,826 --> 00:29:07,871
-Do you think it's Laszlo?
-I don't know.

409
00:29:07,955 --> 00:29:10,332
If he's still around,
why is he being all secret,

410
00:29:10,415 --> 00:29:13,001
like he doesn't want me to see him?

411
00:29:15,587 --> 00:29:19,716
The stories are true.
People are being taken.

412
00:29:19,841 --> 00:29:22,177
We lost Frank today.

413
00:29:23,011 --> 00:29:27,891
He was stolen from right in front of me,
but no more. I swear to you, no more!

414
00:29:28,392 --> 00:29:32,896
Now, I made a pledge that this place
would be a peaceful place,

415
00:29:33,021 --> 00:29:35,857
but now it's time to take up arms.

416
00:29:35,941 --> 00:29:37,025
MEN: Yeah!

417
00:29:37,109 --> 00:29:40,404
We need weapons.
We need sentries on duty.

418
00:29:40,487 --> 00:29:42,781
We need men prepared to fight.

419
00:29:42,864 --> 00:29:48,829
We got to protect ourselves, 'cause you
know no one else will. Now get moving!

420
00:29:49,204 --> 00:29:51,290
Arm yourselves, come on!

421
00:29:51,373 --> 00:29:52,541
MEN: Yeah!

422
00:30:07,014 --> 00:30:09,308
I can't feel my fingers.

423
00:30:09,391 --> 00:30:10,892
(GRUNTING)

424
00:30:12,894 --> 00:30:13,979
(DRILLING)

425
00:30:14,062 --> 00:30:17,691
We can't stay here for much longer.
We'll fall.

426
00:30:18,734 --> 00:30:20,902
Come on, we're nearly done.

427
00:30:29,494 --> 00:30:32,789
The chromatin solution is ready.

428
00:30:32,873 --> 00:30:36,001
Then our preparations are complete.

429
00:30:36,084 --> 00:30:38,670
What are you doing?
Preparations for what?

430
00:30:38,754 --> 00:30:42,591
This is the final experiment.

431
00:30:42,716 --> 00:30:46,928
What do you mean?
Do you mean like those pig-men things?

432
00:30:47,429 --> 00:30:50,432
You're not gonna turn me into
one of those. Oh, God, please don't!

433
00:30:50,515 --> 00:30:53,352
The Pig Slaves are primitive.

434
00:30:53,435 --> 00:30:57,939
The final experiment is greater by far.

435
00:30:59,941 --> 00:31:02,444
But how does that involve me?

436
00:31:02,527 --> 00:31:07,115
We need your flesh. Bring him to me.

437
00:31:07,741 --> 00:31:13,288
Halt! This action contradicts
the Dalek imperative.

438
00:31:13,580 --> 00:31:16,458
Daleks are supreme. Humans are weak.

439
00:31:16,541 --> 00:31:21,880
But there are millions of humans
and only four of us.

440
00:31:21,963 --> 00:31:26,802
If we are supreme,
why are we not victorious?

441
00:31:28,970 --> 00:31:35,394
The Cult of Skaro was created
by the Emperor for this very purpose,

442
00:31:35,477 --> 00:31:39,898
to imagine new ways of survival.

443
00:31:39,981 --> 00:31:42,275
But we must remain pure.

444
00:31:42,359 --> 00:31:47,948
No, Dalek Thay!
Our purity has brought us to extinction!

445
00:31:48,865 --> 00:31:52,244
We must adapt to survive.

446
00:31:52,369 --> 00:31:56,289
You have all made sacrifices.

447
00:31:56,373 --> 00:32:02,796
And now I will sacrifice myself
for the greater cause,

448
00:32:03,338 --> 00:32:09,553
for the future of Dalek-kind.
Now bring me the human!

449
00:32:09,678 --> 00:32:13,765
But I don't understand.
What do you mean? Get off of me.

450
00:32:13,849 --> 00:32:18,145
Behold the true Dalek form.

451
00:32:22,023 --> 00:32:26,570
Now join with me.

452
00:32:27,195 --> 00:32:33,076
No! Get off me!
I did everything you asked of me! No!

453
00:32:47,883 --> 00:32:52,012
That's it, just need to heat you up.

454
00:33:00,187 --> 00:33:02,439
Girls, it's show time!

455
00:33:02,522 --> 00:33:04,774
Lois, you spoil my sashay tonight,

456
00:33:04,858 --> 00:33:07,569
-I'm gonna punch you.
-Quit complaining, Myrna.

457
00:33:07,652 --> 00:33:10,822
-Go buy yourself some glasses.
-Come on, honey, take a look.

458
00:33:10,906 --> 00:33:15,660
-Ever been on stage before?
-Oh, little bit, you know, Shakespeare.

459
00:33:15,744 --> 00:33:18,872
How dull is that?
Come and see a real show!

460
00:33:23,793 --> 00:33:25,754
This is artificial!

461
00:33:27,422 --> 00:33:29,841
ANNOUNCER: Ladies and gentlemen...

462
00:33:29,925 --> 00:33:31,968
They genetically engineered it.

463
00:33:34,346 --> 00:33:37,224
Whoever this is, oh, you're clever.

464
00:33:37,933 --> 00:33:40,936
ANNOUNCER: With Heaven and Hell.

465
00:33:41,019 --> 00:33:42,979
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

466
00:33:43,104 --> 00:33:44,898
(MUSIC PLAYING)

467
00:33:56,576 --> 00:34:00,288
# You lured me in
with your cold grey eyes

468
00:34:00,372 --> 00:34:04,376
# Your simple smile
your bewitching lies

469
00:34:04,459 --> 00:34:08,046
# One and one and one is three

470
00:34:08,129 --> 00:34:10,966
# My bad, bad angel

471
00:34:11,049 --> 00:34:13,969
# The devil and me

472
00:34:14,344 --> 00:34:18,098
# You put the devil in me

473
00:34:18,181 --> 00:34:21,434
# You put the devil in me

474
00:34:21,977 --> 00:34:25,522
# You put the devil in me

475
00:34:27,274 --> 00:34:29,693
# My bad, bad angel

476
00:34:29,776 --> 00:34:32,195
# You put the devil in me #

477
00:34:32,279 --> 00:34:34,197
(AUDIENCE WHISTLING)

478
00:34:48,503 --> 00:34:51,172
What are you doing?

479
00:35:01,558 --> 00:35:02,809
(EXCLAIMS)

480
00:35:03,059 --> 00:35:07,814
-What are you doing?
-You're on my tail. Get off my tail!

481
00:35:08,189 --> 00:35:13,194
Fundamental DNA type 467-989.

482
00:35:14,529 --> 00:35:18,742
989. Hold on,
now that means planet of origin...

483
00:35:23,496 --> 00:35:24,706
Skaro.

484
00:35:27,125 --> 00:35:31,046
-Get off the stage, you're spoiling it.
-But look, over there!

485
00:35:32,505 --> 00:35:34,007
(SCREAMING)

486
00:35:35,425 --> 00:35:36,676
Hey!

487
00:35:40,055 --> 00:35:41,640
Wait!

488
00:35:43,642 --> 00:35:46,728
But you're different to the others.
Just wait.

489
00:35:48,563 --> 00:35:50,106
(CLANKING)

490
00:35:51,274 --> 00:35:53,401
It was like something
out of a movie show.

491
00:35:53,485 --> 00:35:56,237
Oh, that face.
I ain't never gonna sleep.

492
00:35:56,321 --> 00:35:59,449
-Where is she? Where's Martha?
-I don't know. She ran off the stage.

493
00:36:02,702 --> 00:36:03,787
(GRUNTING)

494
00:36:03,912 --> 00:36:05,413
(SCREAMING)

495
00:36:09,959 --> 00:36:11,378
Martha!

496
00:36:17,425 --> 00:36:20,387
-Oh, where are you going?
-They've taken her.

497
00:36:20,470 --> 00:36:23,682
Who's taken her? What are you doing?

498
00:36:24,557 --> 00:36:27,560
I said what the hell are you doing?

499
00:36:28,186 --> 00:36:29,688
(MUMBLING) Crazy guy...

500
00:36:34,776 --> 00:36:37,028
No, no, no, no way. You're not coming.

501
00:36:37,112 --> 00:36:39,906
-Tell me what's going on.
-There's nothing you can do, go back.

502
00:36:39,989 --> 00:36:43,743
Look, whoever's taken Martha they could
have taken Laszlo, couldn't they?

503
00:36:43,827 --> 00:36:47,789
-Tallulah, you're not safe down here.
-Then that's my problem.

504
00:36:47,914 --> 00:36:50,083
Come on. Which way?

505
00:36:53,128 --> 00:36:54,963
This way.

506
00:36:58,842 --> 00:37:00,844
Let me go!

507
00:37:05,515 --> 00:37:09,018
-Martha.
-You're alive.

508
00:37:13,398 --> 00:37:17,944
Oh, I thought we'd lost you.
All right, all right, we're moving!

509
00:37:18,653 --> 00:37:20,572
-Where are they taking us?
-I don't know.

510
00:37:20,655 --> 00:37:22,657
But we can find out
what's going on down here.

511
00:37:26,119 --> 00:37:30,915
When you say they've taken her,
who's they, exactly?

512
00:37:30,999 --> 00:37:33,084
And who are you, anyway? I never asked.

513
00:37:33,168 --> 00:37:34,586
-Shh.
-Okay, okay.

514
00:37:34,669 --> 00:37:36,004
Shh!

515
00:37:39,549 --> 00:37:40,759
I mean, you're a handsome enough...

516
00:37:40,842 --> 00:37:42,177
(MUFFLED SCREAM)

517
00:38:02,030 --> 00:38:04,699
No, no, no.

518
00:38:09,454 --> 00:38:13,708
They survive. They always survive,
while I lose everything.

519
00:38:15,210 --> 00:38:18,379
That metal thing, what was it?

520
00:38:20,256 --> 00:38:22,091
It's called a Dalek.

521
00:38:23,051 --> 00:38:25,887
-And it's not just metal, it's alive.
-You're kidding me.

522
00:38:25,970 --> 00:38:28,097
Do I look like I'm kidding?

523
00:38:30,892 --> 00:38:34,604
Inside that shell
there's a creature born to hate,

524
00:38:34,729 --> 00:38:36,815
who's only thought
is to destroy everything

525
00:38:36,898 --> 00:38:39,567
and everyone that isn't a Dalek too.

526
00:38:41,402 --> 00:38:45,073
They won't stop until it's killed
every human being alive.

527
00:38:45,198 --> 00:38:48,117
But if that's not a human being,

528
00:38:48,201 --> 00:38:52,121
that kind of implies
it's from outer space.

529
00:38:53,873 --> 00:38:57,585
Yet again, that's a no with the kidding.
Oy!

530
00:38:58,878 --> 00:39:02,257
Well, what's it doing here in New York?

531
00:39:04,843 --> 00:39:09,264
Stop the process. Dalek Sec is failing!

532
00:39:09,347 --> 00:39:14,727
No! The experiment must continue.

533
00:39:15,228 --> 00:39:18,022
Administer the solution!

534
00:39:18,857 --> 00:39:21,818
We must evolve.

535
00:39:21,943 --> 00:39:26,030
Evolve! Evolve!

536
00:39:26,239 --> 00:39:29,117
Every second you're down here, you're in
danger. I'm taking you back right now.

537
00:39:29,242 --> 00:39:30,577
(SCREAMING)

538
00:39:31,369 --> 00:39:34,497
Where's Martha?
What have you done with her?

539
00:39:35,748 --> 00:39:39,419
-What have you done with Martha?
-I didn't take her.

540
00:39:39,502 --> 00:39:42,881
-Can you remember your name?
-Don't look at me.

541
00:39:44,799 --> 00:39:48,553
-Do you know where she is?
-Stay back! Don't look at me.

542
00:39:48,636 --> 00:39:51,723
-What happened to you?
-They made me a monster.

543
00:39:51,806 --> 00:39:54,267
-Who did?
-The masters.

544
00:39:54,350 --> 00:39:57,020
The Daleks. Why?

545
00:39:57,103 --> 00:39:59,063
They needed slaves.

546
00:40:00,815 --> 00:40:02,901
They needed slaves to steal more people,

547
00:40:02,984 --> 00:40:07,572
so they created us,
part animal, part human.

548
00:40:08,781 --> 00:40:13,661
I escaped before they got my mind
but it was still too late.

549
00:40:14,662 --> 00:40:17,290
Do you know what happened to Martha?

550
00:40:18,291 --> 00:40:23,212
They took her. It's my fault,
she was following me.

551
00:40:23,713 --> 00:40:25,840
Were you in the theatre?

552
00:40:25,924 --> 00:40:27,634
I never...

553
00:40:28,760 --> 00:40:31,971
-Yes.
-Why? Why were you there?

554
00:40:32,055 --> 00:40:34,599
I never wanted you to see me like this.

555
00:40:34,682 --> 00:40:38,478
Why me? What I got to do with this?

556
00:40:39,395 --> 00:40:42,774
Were you following me?
Is that why you were there?

557
00:40:46,027 --> 00:40:47,528
Yes.

558
00:40:51,157 --> 00:40:54,160
-Who are you?
-I was lonely.

559
00:40:54,994 --> 00:40:58,164
-Who are you?
-I needed to see you.

560
00:40:58,289 --> 00:41:00,333
Who are you?

561
00:41:02,460 --> 00:41:05,004
-I'm sorry.
-No, wait.

562
00:41:07,507 --> 00:41:09,717
Let me look at you.

563
00:41:18,476 --> 00:41:20,061
Laszlo?

564
00:41:21,396 --> 00:41:23,022
My Laszlo?

565
00:41:24,857 --> 00:41:27,694
What have they done to you?

566
00:41:28,653 --> 00:41:31,614
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

567
00:41:33,199 --> 00:41:37,578
-Laszlo, can you show me where they are?
-But they'll kill you.

568
00:41:37,662 --> 00:41:40,665
If I don't stop them,
they'll kill everyone.

569
00:41:46,587 --> 00:41:48,214
Then follow me.

570
00:41:51,843 --> 00:41:55,179
-What are they keeping us here for?
-I don't know.

571
00:41:55,263 --> 00:41:57,181
Got a nasty feeling we're being
kept in the larder.

572
00:41:59,308 --> 00:42:01,144
(SNORTING)

573
00:42:02,854 --> 00:42:05,106
What are they doing? What's wrong?
What's wrong?

574
00:42:05,189 --> 00:42:08,151
Silence! Silence!

575
00:42:09,777 --> 00:42:11,654
What the hell is that?

576
00:42:14,282 --> 00:42:17,785
You will form a line! Move! Move!

577
00:42:17,952 --> 00:42:20,496
Just do what it says, everyone, okay?
Just obey.

578
00:42:20,580 --> 00:42:24,959
The female is wise. Obey!

579
00:42:25,084 --> 00:42:29,047
-Report!
-These are strong specimens.

580
00:42:29,130 --> 00:42:31,632
They will help the Dalek cause.

581
00:42:31,799 --> 00:42:32,842
Dalek.

582
00:42:32,925 --> 00:42:36,637
What is the status
of the final experiment?

583
00:42:36,721 --> 00:42:42,268
The Dalekenium is in place.
The energy conductor is now complete.

584
00:42:42,769 --> 00:42:46,314
Then I will extract prisoners
for selection.

585
00:42:47,607 --> 00:42:50,985
Intelligence scan - initiate.

586
00:42:52,987 --> 00:42:57,825
Reading brainwaves. Low intelligence.

587
00:42:58,034 --> 00:43:00,328
-You calling me stupid?
-Silence!

588
00:43:00,411 --> 00:43:03,581
This one will become a Pig Slave. Next.

589
00:43:03,664 --> 00:43:06,375
No, let go of me!
I'm not becoming one of them.

590
00:43:06,459 --> 00:43:08,169
No, let me go!

591
00:43:08,252 --> 00:43:12,006
Intelligence scan - initiate.

592
00:43:12,632 --> 00:43:17,637
They're divided into two groups:
high intelligence and low intelligence.

593
00:43:18,054 --> 00:43:22,350
The low intelligence are taken
to become Pig Slaves, like me.

594
00:43:22,558 --> 00:43:24,685
-But that's not fair!
-Shh!

595
00:43:24,769 --> 00:43:26,771
You're the smartest guy I ever dated.

596
00:43:26,854 --> 00:43:30,108
-And the others?
-They're taken to the laboratory.

597
00:43:30,191 --> 00:43:33,152
-Why? What for?
-I don't know.

598
00:43:34,195 --> 00:43:38,116
The masters only call it
the final experiment.

599
00:43:38,324 --> 00:43:40,535
Superior intelligence.

600
00:43:42,078 --> 00:43:45,748
Intelligence scan - initiate.

601
00:43:47,375 --> 00:43:50,169
Superior intelligence.

602
00:43:50,253 --> 00:43:54,215
This one will become part
of the final experiment.

603
00:43:54,298 --> 00:43:57,969
You can't just experiment on people.
It's insane! It's inhuman!

604
00:43:58,052 --> 00:44:00,304
We are not human.

605
00:44:02,723 --> 00:44:08,563
Prisoners of high intelligence will be
taken to the Transgenic Laboratory.

606
00:44:09,564 --> 00:44:11,649
Look out, they're moving.

607
00:44:14,193 --> 00:44:15,820
Doctor. Doctor, quickly!

608
00:44:15,903 --> 00:44:17,864
I'm not coming.
I've got an idea. You go.

609
00:44:17,947 --> 00:44:20,658
-Laszlo, come on.
-Can you remember the way?

610
00:44:20,741 --> 00:44:22,743
-Yeah, I think so.
-Then go, please.

611
00:44:22,827 --> 00:44:24,203
But, Laszlo, you've got to come with me.

612
00:44:24,287 --> 00:44:25,913
Where would I go?

613
00:44:26,164 --> 00:44:30,251
Tallulah, I'm begging you.
Just save yourself, just run. Just go!

614
00:44:31,627 --> 00:44:32,837
Go.

615
00:44:44,348 --> 00:44:47,602
-Keep walking.
-I am so glad to see you.

616
00:44:47,727 --> 00:44:52,398
Yeah, well, you can kiss me later.
You, too, Frank, if you want.

617
00:45:28,809 --> 00:45:30,186
Report!

618
00:45:30,311 --> 00:45:34,899
Dalek Sec is entering
the final stage of evolution.

619
00:45:34,982 --> 00:45:38,402
Scan him. Prepare for birth.

620
00:45:38,486 --> 00:45:39,987
Evolution?

621
00:45:40,071 --> 00:45:42,323
What's wrong with
old Charlie Boy over there?

622
00:45:42,406 --> 00:45:46,327
-DOCTOR: Ask them.
-What, me? Don't be daft.

623
00:45:46,702 --> 00:45:50,706
I don't exactly want to get noticed.
Ask them what's going on.

624
00:45:54,919 --> 00:45:57,713
Daleks, I demand to be told.

625
00:45:58,089 --> 00:46:01,467
What is this final experiment?

626
00:46:02,843 --> 00:46:04,011
Report!

627
00:46:04,387 --> 00:46:08,182
-You will bear witness.
-To what?

628
00:46:08,516 --> 00:46:12,144
This is the dawn of a new age.

629
00:46:13,729 --> 00:46:15,189
What does that mean?

630
00:46:15,273 --> 00:46:19,443
We are the only four Daleks
in existence.

631
00:46:19,527 --> 00:46:22,154
So the species must evolve.

632
00:46:22,238 --> 00:46:25,533
A life outside the shell.

633
00:46:25,616 --> 00:46:29,870
The children of Skaro must walk again.

634
00:47:02,069 --> 00:47:03,654
What is it?

635
00:47:15,207 --> 00:47:20,838
I am a human Dalek.

636
00:47:22,131 --> 00:47:26,135
I am your future.

637
00:48:20,981 --> 00:48:22,566
Move, move, move, move, move!

638
00:48:22,650 --> 00:48:24,235
Come on, everyone up, come on!

639
00:48:24,652 --> 00:48:28,030
Daleks are bad enough at any time,
but right now they're vulnerable.

640
00:48:28,114 --> 00:48:29,949
That makes them
more dangerous than ever.

641
00:48:30,074 --> 00:48:32,118
Monsters! They're monsters!

642
00:48:32,201 --> 00:48:33,244
It's started.

643
00:48:33,327 --> 00:48:34,537
(SQUEALING)

644
00:48:34,620 --> 00:48:35,830
DOCTOR: Got to get everyone out.

645
00:48:35,913 --> 00:48:37,790
SOLOMON: Hooverville's the lowest place
a man can fall

646
00:48:37,873 --> 00:48:39,291
there's nowhere else to go.

647
00:48:39,375 --> 00:48:42,002
-Oh, my God.
-Take aim.

648
00:48:44,463 --> 00:48:45,714
(SCREAMING)

649
00:48:46,507 --> 00:48:47,550
(SCREAMING)

650
00:48:47,633 --> 00:48:49,218
Exterminate.

